 1992-07501992-04-090,  ISTC,  ,  , 
PrecisRe-appointment of Albert W. Diamond, of Val d'Or, Quebec, as a member of the Eastern Aboriginal Economic Development Board and designation of the said Albert W. Diamond as Chairperson thereof, for a term of three years, effective February 10, 1992; re-appointment of certain persons as members of the Eastern Aboriginal Economic Development Board for a term of three years, effective February 10, 1992; and appointment of certain persons as members of the Eastern Aboriginal Economic Development Board for a term of three years. (John Kime, Toronto, Ontario; James P. Ward, Newcastle, New Brunswick; Ruth K. Corbett, Kakabeka Falls, Ontario, in the place of Kaaydah B. Schatten; Minnie Grey, Kuujjuaq, Quebec; and Judy Cooko-Whiteduck, Maniwaki, Quebec)
